    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-12T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-12T11:00:00-05:00" n="151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/5–1254: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">Smith</persName>—<persName corresp="#p_EA1"
                            >Eden</persName>—<persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> Meeting,
                        Geneva, May 12, Noon: The <gloss type="from">United States
                            Delegation</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-12T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 12, 1954—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 182. Repeated information Seoul 68,
                    Tokyo 50. Tokyo for <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss>. At meeting of
                    heads of Big Three delegations this noon, General <persName corresp="#p_SWB1"
                        >Smith</persName> explained futility of engaging in endless attempt to work
                    out details of plan with <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> when any
                    solution we proposed must be based on authority of <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss>, which <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> had
                    yesterday categorically rejected. He explained why we should not press <persName
                        corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> too hard, including need for Congressional
                    support on Indochina. He also mentioned possibility of suggesting, in restricted
                    meeting of seven, regrouping of Chinese and <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>
                    forces prior to elections. We had reached an impasse and there would be no
                    communist concessions. <persName corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> was right
                    that North Korea had become a Chinese province. It had gone and we were not
                    going to fight global war for it. Issue should be joined on whether or not
                    communists would accept <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> authority.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_EA1">Eden</persName> said he wanted to speak next plenary
                    in reply to <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> and particularly to
                    discuss question of where freedom was found in Asia. He would also like to speak
                    on principles. It was agreed that <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName>
                    would speak first in general terms, that <persName corresp="#p_EA1"
                        >Eden</persName> would then follow up with statement of principles and that
                    Asian representative, presumably Philippines, would if possible obtain 16
                    agreement present specific proposal on principles. <persName corresp="#p_SWB1"
                        >Smith</persName> suggested it be put to communists on <pb facs="0284"
                        n="258" xml:id="pg_258"/> basis that if they accepted, there would be
                    further discussion in restricted sessions, otherwise, there would seem to be no
                    further point in continuing Korean discussion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
